    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the base of your <strong>living lettuce </strong>then wash the <strong>living lettuce</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> and cut away the core, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>living lettuce leaves</strong> from the stem until you are left with a pile of leaves</p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely and add them to a small bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mix it all together – this is your<strong> chive dressing</strong></p>",
